FBIS4-60538 "drnes102_w_94002" FBIS-NES-94-102 Daily Report 23 May 1994 Sri Lanka Prime Minister Leaves for ROK Visit Prime Minister Leaves for ROK Visit BK2305161494 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation International Service in English 1045 GMT 23 May 94 BK2305161494 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation International Service English BFN [Text] Sri Lanka will sign a science and technology agreement with South Korea. Prime Minister Ranil Wickremasinghe left for South Korea on an official visit last night. He will sign an agreement with his counterpart Yi Yong-tok [name as heard]. The prime minister is also expected to hold talks with potential investors and industrialists. High-level officials of major Korean industries are expected to meet Mr. Wickremasinghe. He is scheduled to tour industrial zones in the country. South Korean cooperation will be sought to establish technical training institutes and to train our youths in that country. Leading local businessmen are simultaneously visiting South Korea to hold discussions on prospective investments and trade promotion.
